{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idcb3cd72a-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s24907"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"24907"},"text":"§ 24907.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Note and mortgage","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idcb3cd72b-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s24907/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"General Authority","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"To secure amounts expended by the United States Government to acquire and improve rail property designated under section 206(c)(1)(C) and (D) of the Regional Rail Reorganization Act of 1973 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t45/s716/c/1/C"},"text":"45 U.S.C. 716(c)(1)(C)","children":[],"tail":" and (D)), the Secretary of Transportation may obtain a note of indebtedness from, and make a mortgage agreement with, Amtrak to establish a mortgage lien on the property for the Government. The note and mortgage may not supersede section 24903."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idcb3cd72c-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s24907/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Exemptions From Laws and Regulations","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The note and agreement under subsection (a) of this section, and a transaction related to the note or agreement, are exempt from any United States, State, or local law or regulation that regulates securities or the issuance of securities. The note, agreement, or transaction under this section has the same immunities from other laws that section 601 of the Act (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t45/s791"},"text":"45 U.S.C. 791","children":[],"tail":") gives to transactions that comply with or carry out the final system plan. The transfer of rail property because of the note, agreement, or transaction has the same exemptions, privileges, and immunities that the Act ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t45/s701"},"text":"45 U.S.C. 701","children":[],"tail":" et seq.) gives to a transfer ordered or approved by the special court under section 303(b) of the Act ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t45/s743/b"},"text":"45 U.S.C. 743(b)","children":[],"tail":")."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idcb3cd72d-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s24907/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Immunity From Liability and Indemnification","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"Amtrak, its board of directors, and its individual directors are not liable because Amtrak has given or issued the note or agreement to the Government under subsection (a) of this section. Immunity granted under this subsection also applies to a transaction related to the note or agreement. The Government shall indemnify Amtrak, its board, and individual directors against costs and expenses actually and reasonably incurred in defending a civil action testing the validity of the note, agreement, or transaction.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idcb3cd72e-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/272/s1/e"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–272, § 1(e)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-07-05"},"text":"July 5, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/936"},"text":"108 Stat. 936","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/94/dA/tXI/s11306/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–94, div. A, title XI, § 11306(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2015-12-04"},"text":"Dec. 4, 2015","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/129/1660"},"text":"129 Stat. 1660","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idcb3cd72f-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idcb3cd730-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:table","attrib":{"width":"50%","id":"idcb3cd731-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:colgroup","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:thead","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{"colspan":"3"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Revised","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Section","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Source (U.S. Code)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Source (Statutes at Large)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tbody","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"24907(a)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"45:854(e).","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Feb. 5, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/210"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–210","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/31"},"text":"90 Stat. 31","children":[],"tail":", § 704(e)–(g); added "},{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Oct. 19, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/555/s217/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–555, § 217(c)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/2627"},"text":"90 Stat. 2627","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"24907(b)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"45:854(f).","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"24907(c)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"45:854(g).","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (a), the words “In order . . . protect and”, “securing such expenditure”, “infringe upon or”, and “the authority conferred upon the National Railroad Passenger Corporation by” are omitted as surplus.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsections (b) and (c), the words “note” and “agreement” are substituted for “agreement, security, or obligation” for consistency because the Secretary of Transportation gets only notes and mortgage agreements under the source provisions restated in subsection (a) of this section.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (b), the words “obtained by the Secretary” and “the provisions of subtitle IV of title 49, the Securities Act of 1933 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s77a"},"text":"15 U.S.C. 77a","children":[],"tail":" et seq.), and . . . other” are omitted as surplus. The words “has the same” are substituted for “shall enjoy all of the” for clarity. The words “conveyance or” are omitted, and the word “transfer” is substituted for “conveyances”, for consistency in this subtitle. The words “(including section 303(e) thereof ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t45/s743/e"},"text":"45 U.S.C. 743(e)","children":[],"tail":"])” are omitted as surplus. The words “section 303(b)” are substituted for “section 306(b)” to correct a mistake in section 217(c) of the Rail Transportation Improvement Act ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/555"},"text":"Public Law 94–555","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/2628"},"text":"90 Stat. 2628","children":[],"tail":")."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (c), the words “to any party for any damages, or in any other matter” are omitted as surplus. The word “because” is substituted for ‘by reason of the fact that” to eliminate unnecessary words. The words “related to the note or agreement” are substituted for “in connection with” for clarity. The words “all” and “(including fees of accountants, experts, and attorneys)” are omitted as surplus. The words “a civil action” are substituted for “any litigation” for consistency with rule 2 of the Federal Rules of Civil Procedure (28 App. U.S.C.). The words “legal” and “given, issued, or entered into” are omitted as surplus.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idcb3cd732-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idcb3cd733-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Regional Rail Reorganization Act of 1973, referred to in subsecs. (a) and (b), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/236"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–236","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1974-01-02"},"text":"Jan. 2, 1974","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/87/985"},"text":"87 Stat. 985","children":[],"tail":", which is classified principally to chapter 16 (§ 701 et seq.) of Title 45, Railroads. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t45/s701"},"text":"section 701 of Title 45","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idcb3cd734-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2015—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/94"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–94","children":[],"tail":" substituted “section 24903” for “"},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t49/s24904"},"text":"section 24904 of this title","children":[],"tail":"”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idcb3cd735-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idcb3cd736-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2015 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/94"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–94","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2015-10-01"},"text":"Oct. 1, 2015","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/94/s1003"},"text":"section 1003 of Pub. L. 114–94","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s5313"},"text":"section 5313 of Title 5","children":[],"tail":", Government Organization and Employees."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idcb3cd737-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Abolition of Special Court, Regional Rail Reorganization Act of 1973, and Transfer of Functions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Special court abolished and all jurisdiction and functions transferred to United States District Court for District of Columbia, see ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t45/s719/b/2"},"text":"section 719(b)(2) of Title 45","children":[],"tail":", Railroads."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
